Pre-requisites : 4GB RAM for the instance

UBUNTU

Install java first:
====================

sudo apt-get update

sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y



get the package :
================
echo "deb https://releases.jfrog.io/artifactory/artifactory-debs focal main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jfrog.list

sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install jfrog-artifactory-oss -y




edit the file:
================

sudo systemctl edit artifactory

[Service]
Environment=ARTIFACTORY_HOME=/opt/jfrog/artifactory


install postgresql
=================

sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib

sudo systemctl start postgresql
sudo systemctl enable postgresql

sudo -u postgres psql

CREATE USER artifactory WITH PASSWORD 'artifactory';
CREATE DATABASE artifactory_db OWNER artifactory;
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE artifactory_db TO artifactory;
\q

sudo vi /var/opt/jfrog/artifactory/etc/system.yaml

uncomment and edit the lines in the file
=======================================

database:
  type: postgresql
  driver: org.postgresql.Driver
  url: jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/artifactory_db
  username: artifactory
  password: artifactory


sudo systemctl start artifactory
sudo systemctl status artifactory
sudo systemctl enable artifactory

to check logs:
===============

sudo tail -f /opt/jfrog/artifactory/var/log/artifactory-service.log


Access jfrog
============
http://<public-i.p>:8081






